Napoli with Super Eagles striker, Victor Osimhen are aiming to take a step closer to claiming their first Scudetto since 1990 when they host Milan at the Diego Armando Maradona Stadium, Naples tomorrow. And with both sides currently level on points at the top with 57 points after 27 matches, it will be a fascinating spectacle. AC Milan were held to a 0-0 draw in the first leg of the Coppa Italia semi-final   ‘We have taken steps to reposition Lobi Stars’     Nigeria v Ghana: Ighalo’s inclusion raises doubt     Troost-Ekong ruled out of clash against Ghana   Napoli are hoping to continue to keep AC Milan below them with a win or a draw before their fans and Luciano Spalletti’s men go into this game off back of a 2-1 win over Lazio and should be the fresher of the two having had a week off. As for AC Milan, they were forced into a midweek 0-0 stalemate against bitter rivals, Inter in the Coppa Italia semi-final first leg. To make matters worse,18-time  Serie A winners are winless in their last two league games so their fans will be putting them under pressure to return to winning ways and thus overtake the Partenopei at the summit. The sides last met in December when Napoli ran out 1-0 winners at San Siro.